      <h3 class="section-title">Intro to Candlesticks</h3>
      <p class="muted">Open / High / Low / Close — simple reading method:</p>
      <div style="display:grid;grid-template-columns:repeat(auto-fit,minmax(220px,1fr));gap:12px;margin-top:12px">
        <div class="card">
          <h4>Bullish Engulfing</h4>
          <p class="muted">Strong sign of reversal when a green candle fully engulfs prior red candle.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="card">
          <h4>Hammer</h4>
          <p class="muted">Small body, long lower wick — buyer pressure near support.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="card">
          <h4>Shooting Star</h4>
          <p class="muted">Top wick after uptrend — possible reversal or exhaustion.</p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>

    <section id="read2" style="padding-top:10px">
      <h3 class="section-title">Moving Average Crossover</h3>
      <p class="muted">Use EMA(9) & EMA(21) for trend confirmation. Entry when 9 crosses above 21 with volume.</p>
      <div style="display:flex;gap:12px;flex-wrap:wrap;margin-top:12px">
        <div class="card" style="min-width:220px">
          <h4>Entry</h4>
          <p class="muted">Buy when 9 EMA crosses above 21 EMA and structure supports trade.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="card" style="min-width:220px">
          <h4>Stop</h4>
          <p class="muted">Place stop below recent swing low or candle low.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="card" style="min-width:220px">
          <h4>Target</h4>
          <p class="muted">Set 1.5–3x reward:risk depending on volatility.</p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>

    <section id="read3" style="padding-top:10px">
      <h3 class="section-title">Position Sizing</h3>
      <p class="muted">Decide risk per trade (e.g., 1% of account). Calculate qty using stop distance.</p>
      <div style="display:flex;gap:12px;margin-top:12px;flex-wrap:wrap">
        <div class="card">
          <h4>Example</h4>
          <p class="muted">Account ₹50,000; risk 1% → ₹500 risk. If stop 25 points → lot/qty = 500/25 = 20 shares.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="card">
          <h4>Tip</h4>
          <p class="muted">Round down quantity; preserve capital.</p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>

